latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Where did the spring season go? 

Where is the pleasant weather of Spring that brings back life to Earth again, when fresh buds bloom, animals awaken, birds sing, vibrant green leaves sprout, bumblebees and butterflies return! 

There’s missing colours and joy and warmth, The spring season has been beset by the scorching heat... 
 
While the industry is working on solutions to combat our greatest threat i.e climate change, It is our collective responsibility to help accelerate the transition to an equitable and prosperous green environment for all. To redirect our attention on creating an ecosystem that brings back the health of our planet...

On this world earth day 2022, I pledge to focus on “reframing conversations and the relationship we have with nature”, for this, I choose to stand with a macaw, a symbol of sacred union and lasting relationships...

This is within our reach if we work jointly ♥️

#WhereisSpring #InvestInOurPlanet #WhatWillYouDo #InDefenceofthePlanet #EnvironmentalEducation

Special Thanks, @ihimanshuarya @rakshit_arya @ishwin._

latestPosts.caption:
As 2024 comes to a close, Idk who needs to hear this but here’s a little reminder for you: success isn’t always measured in grand milestones or big wins. Progress—no matter how small—is the real success story.

If you’ve stood up for yourself, fought back challenges, taken even the tiniest steps forward, or simply made it through tough days, you’ve made this year meaningful. Growth isn’t always loud or visible, but it’s powerful and worth celebrating…
 
I may not be exactly where I envisioned myself, but I’ve grown, progressed, and made it this far—and that’s something to be proud of. ❤️

#EndOfYearReflection #ProgressOverPerfection #CelebrateGrowth #SmallStepsBigWins #Gratitude2024 #PersonalGrowthJourney #HereForTheRide #Bye2024 #Hello2025 #2024recap 
#lastpostoftheyear #lastoftheyear #smallstepseveryday #smallstepstobigchange #selfhealingjourney #selfhealingpower #progressisprogress 

[2024, Hello 2025, End Year,Reflections, Self Growth Journey]

2024: The Comeback

The word ‘comeback’ often brings to mind grand achievements, vibrant celebrations, and undeniable success. My year didn’t look anything like that. 
But I’d still call it a comeback because, in my own way, I made it through. I got back to work, returned to being active on Instagram again, focused on my mental and physical fitness, and pushed myself every single day.

I had the privilege of collaborating with two global luxury brands—a milestone that reaffirmed my belief in my journey. 🙏🏼

At 26, stepping back into this space felt very different from when I started at 17. The uncertainty, self-doubt, fear of failure, and judgment weighed heavily on me. Reviving a dormant Instagram account was no small feat—follower counts were dropping, engagement was low, and algorithms seemed to work completely against me.
My mantra became: “Do internships of your own.” This mindset gave me the freedom to make mistakes without the overwhelming pressure of presenting myself as a professional. 

I was all about rediscovering comfort and purpose, with a renewed determination to thrive.

As expected, the beginning came with its share of rejections, NOs, and challenges. The first step is always the hardest. 
But I’m proud to say I survived and revived my presence in this overwhelming, competitive space. 😌

2024 may not have been filled with grand victories, but it was my foundation year—once again. I’m stepping into 2025 with fresh energy, a vision, and the drive to take another step forward. ❤️💯

#vision2025 #thankyou2024 #contentcreationjourney #hello2025
